snippet: The Pakistan military said five hide-outs were destroyed through “precision airstrikes” in the town of Datta Khel and the Shawal Valley.
abstract: Pakistani jets bomb North Waziristan tribal region along the Pakistan-Afghan border, killing 65 militants.
lead_paragraph: The Pakistan military said five hide-outs were destroyed through “precision airstrikes” in the town of Datta Khel and the Shawal Valley.

headline.main: At Least 65 Militants Killed in Airstrikes, Pakistan Says
headline.print_headline: Pakistan: Military Says Airstrikes Killed 65 Militants
